column5: tons of deer hair, and some feathers.  can include bass too, they'll take a baby duck
Them creature lures seem to have been a lot more common years ago. Ducks, muskrat, giant frogs lures were common years ago.
seeing pike hit topwater never gets tiring. would love to throw those ducks in some prime pike waters.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IyvCQVbm1Cs  Looks to work for Wels Catfish also
Kittens work great too.  I have seen a Musky or Pike come up and take the last duckling paddling along on a bay at Nippising. The Mother duck went berserk.
Westin has "Danny the duck" too.  Also, this...  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2_E4BUt1z8Y  Cheers, Mark
